title: PPPP’s Sher Muhammad wins PS-1 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Sher Muhammad Mugheri has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-1, Jacobabad-I by securing 48,385 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Abdur Razzaq Khan, independent who bagged 18,115 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 37.26%.
